President Uhuru Kenyatta has promoted 22 senior military officers and
appointed some of them to new positions. In the changes cutting across the Kenya Army, Navy and Air Force, Major General Peter Mbogo Njiru, who previously served as President Uhuru's aide-de-camp (ADC), has been promoted
to Lieutenant General and appointed the new Commander of the Kenya Army to replace outgoing Lt Gen Walter
Koipaton who retires on completion of his four-year tenure. In the Kenya Army, Brigadiers
David Kimaiyo Chemwaina Tarus, Jurna Shee Mwinyikai, Fredrick Leuria and Mungai
Nyaga, all from the Army were promoted to Major General positions and handed new roles. Kimaiyo becomes
the General Officer Commanding
Western Command, Mwinyikai the GO Commanding Eastern Command and Leuria the new
Assistant Chief of Defence Forces in charge of Operations, Plans, Doctrine and
Training. Nyaga likewise is
the new Force Commander in the East African Community Regional Force for DRC.  In the Air Force,
Brigadier Benard Waliaula was promoted to Major General assuming the Director
of Defence National Security Industries position. The Ministry of Defence, in a statement issued on Wednesday, said President Kenyatta's decision came after a
joint meeting of
the Defence Council, chaired by Defence Cabinet Secretary Eugene
Wamalwa.  Kenya Army  Kenya Airforce  Kenya Navy   The ministry also noted that similar changes had been made across the Kenya Defence Forces in line with the advice of the Defence Council.